								<h3>Our Mission</h3>
								<p><strong>One out of every five</strong> students report being bullied.<sup><cite><a
												href="https://nces.ed.gov/pubs2019/2019054.pdf">1</a></cite></sup> Students who experience
									bullying are at increased risk for depression, anxiety, sleep difficulties, lower academic
									achievement, dropping out of school, and various negative health effects.<sup><cite><a
												href="https://www.cdc.gov/violenceprevention/pdf/yv/bullying-factsheet508.pdf">2</a></cite></sup>
									Our mission at Anti-Bullying Scorecard is to illuminate parents' voices to help schools recognize what
									is both effective and ineffective with their policies.</p>
								<p>Studies show that a solid school-based bullying prevention program has the ability to decrease
									bullying by up to 25%. With your voice, we can help improve the well-being of our next generation.</p>
								<p><a class="btn_1 add_top_10 wow bounceIn" href="/signup" data-wow-delay="0.5s">Join Us Now!</a>
